    "updated_at": "2012-01-05T14:19:11Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Ultratb also monkeypatches `inspect.findsource()`, for Python 2.5 and above, seemingly to fix a bug where `codeobj.co_firstlineno` can be greater than the number of lines in the file. It's not clear when that bug occurs, or whether it has since been fixed. I think it might make sense to drop the monkeypatch, and catch exceptions from findsource().\n"
  },
