    "created_at": "2012-01-12T06:27:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-12T06:27:15Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Mmh, if the calls aren't made by us, then it may be necessary to keep the monkeypatch then.  I'm just worried that it was added to protect against errors seen in the field, and we may get those back if we remove it.\n\nIt's a bummer that a while back, we added so many of these things without a corresponding test to validate the problem, so we could know whether the patch was still required.  For all we know, python 2.6 or 2.7 may have fixed this issue...\n\nAbsent a place to catch the exception ourselves, I'm inclined to back off that last commit, what do you think?\n"
  },
