    "created_at": "2012-01-12T10:53:07Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-12T10:53:07Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We could do, but I'm a bit concerned that, since we don't know exactly what caused the bug, we're left with a monkeypatch that can never be removed, while we may be missing improvements in the Python findsource() code.\n\nWhat about this: I leave the modified function in the file, but comment out the line monkeypatching it into inspect, with an explanatory note. I imagine there's a few months before we release 0.13, so if no-one's seen the bug by then, it's either fixed, or a very rare occurrence. If we do see it, then we'll either put the monkeypatch back with a more detailed description, or work out a better fix.\n"
  },
